Definition: cater to popular taste to make popular and present to the general public
Example: bring into general or common use; They popularized coffee in Washington State; Relativity Theory was vulgarized by these authors
Synonyms: noun, act, popularization, person, popularizer, popularise, popularisation, populariser, vulgarize, adj, all, lowborn, vulgar, vulgarization, vulgarizer, vulgarise, vulgarisation, vulgariser, generalize, generalise, disseminate, cater, to, popular, taste, make, and, present, the, general, public, bring, into, or, common, use, They, popularized, coffee, in, Washington, State, Relativity, Theory, was, vulgarized, by, these, authors
